1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,100
hello everyone

2
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:04,266
today we are going to start a new season of GragTech New Horizons

3
00:00:04,266 --> 00:00:06,233
unlike the previous season

4
00:00:06,366 --> 00:00:08,200
we are not going to ditch the quest book

5
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:10,466
but we are going to follow it more strictly

6
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:12,833
the first thing we are asked to do

7
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:14,200
is to gather some dirt

8
00:00:14,233 --> 00:00:16,166
which we can use to hide ourselves

9
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:19,000
if we can't get a bed in time for the first night

10
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,633
but that won't be an issue

11
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:24,166
since we managed to locate an abandoned building that we can shelter

12
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:26,166
and there we also found a bed

13
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:30,266
that will allow us to get some rest before moving on with the next task

14
00:00:30,266 --> 00:00:32,200
getting some wood and some gravel

15
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,700
while wood is everywhere

16
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,266
finding gravel is a little bit trickier

17
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:39,166
the easiest way is probably to just look for a river

18
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:40,300
and check on its bed

19
00:00:40,566 --> 00:00:42,233
one thing you'll probably notice

20
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,033
is that unlike vanilla Minecraft

21
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:46,300
you won't be getting any flint out of it

22
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:47,466
to obtain flint

23
00:00:47,466 --> 00:00:50,233
you have to smash together three blocks of gravel

24
00:00:50,666 --> 00:00:52,633
and that was also another quest

25
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:53,500
with that flint

26
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:56,366
we can now craft a rather expensive crafting table

27
00:00:56,366 --> 00:00:58,000
and an axe and

28
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,500
flint is also going to be the material for our first tools

29
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,566
now that we have the basic equipment

30
00:01:03,566 --> 00:01:08,366
we can start our journey of the self imposed challenge of completing every quest

31
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:09,300
to do that

32
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,433
we had to adventure across all sorts of biomes

33
00:01:12,866 --> 00:01:15,833
we crossed dry biomes to find quick sands

34
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:18,666
we crossed a lake to find a magical forest

35
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:21,466
the only place where a rare blue tree grows

36
00:01:21,566 --> 00:01:23,600
finally after crossing a Canyon

37
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:27,800
we managed to find a rare forest of bamboo for our last quest

38
00:01:27,966 --> 00:01:29,233
once we get back home

39
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:33,800
we can brew a nice cup of tea before getting to the next chapter of quests

40
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:34,633
tier 0

41
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,000
this is the Stone Age level

42
00:01:37,066 --> 00:01:39,766
so we have to start by doing some heavy work

43
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,833
and after gathering enough materials

44
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:44,433
we can craft enough bricks for a cook oven

45
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,233
we will momentorily build it under the floor

46
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,466
so that we can easily fuel the furnaces

47
00:01:49,466 --> 00:01:51,866
that will polish the stone for our house

48
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:54,666
meanwhile we also built a small workshop

49
00:01:54,666 --> 00:01:56,666
where we can craft better tools

50
00:01:57,666 --> 00:01:59,900
it is composed of 3 tables

51
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:02,800
the first two will allow us to create patterns

52
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,633
and parts for the new tools

53
00:02:04,866 --> 00:02:07,800
we can use all kind of easy to mold materials

54
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:09,966
the last table is the one

55
00:02:09,966 --> 00:02:12,866
we used to assemble the parts into new tools

56
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,433
now that we have a pickaxe it is time to go mining

57
00:02:17,166 --> 00:02:18,866
but we won't go in caves

58
00:02:18,866 --> 00:02:21,566
or random holes like in normal Minecraft

59
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,800
in this modpack

60
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:26,466
ores spawn in a huge cluster located in a grid pattern

61
00:02:27,066 --> 00:02:27,600
that means

62
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:30,200
we just have to dig at the center of the grid cells

63
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,400
to find clusters of minerals

64
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:35,000
and in this location we found oil sands

65
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,066
which we don't really need at the moment

66
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,166
so we move on to the next one

67
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:42,233
and after some digging we found limonite

68
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,000
an iron rich mineral

69
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:47,233
but it looks like our flint pickaxe can't break it

70
00:02:47,466 --> 00:02:47,900
luckily

71
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:52,233
our quest book traded us an iron pickaxe head for some cobblestone

72
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:57,600
we can use a tool station to repair and upgrade our pickaxes with the newly acquired part

73
00:02:58,566 --> 00:03:01,100
and with that we can finally collect iron

74
00:03:01,366 --> 00:03:04,233
the other nice feature of our new pickaxes is that

75
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:05,266
the more we use it

76
00:03:05,266 --> 00:03:06,766
the more it will level up

77
00:03:06,966 --> 00:03:08,966
this will give modifier slots

78
00:03:08,966 --> 00:03:12,933
which will allow us to add some enchanting materials to our tools

79
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:13,666
for example

80
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:19,633
we can add some lapis lazuli to our pickaxes to increase the amount of ore it harvests

81
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,166
one other useful modifier is Redstone

82
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:26,100
which will increase the working speed of our tools

83
00:03:26,233 --> 00:03:27,900
next we built a smeltery

84
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,300
which is a variable size structure

85
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,200
which will allow us to melt metals

86
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,300
and cast parts for our tools

87
00:03:34,566 --> 00:03:38,133
but tools made like that are just for the basic world interactions

88
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:40,466
to craft more advanced equipment

89
00:03:40,466 --> 00:03:42,633

we need more refined tools


90
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:44,233
there are a lot of those

91
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:46,666
but we can start just with the basic ones

92
00:03:47,266 --> 00:03:48,033
and with those

93
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:50,966
we can now work iron in all sorts of components

94
00:03:51,466 --> 00:03:53,300
in case you are wondering what for

95
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,433
consider that doors are held together with screws

96
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,033
with all of those new parts

97
00:03:58,033 --> 00:04:00,033
we can now craft many new things

98
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,100
we can start with a new lunch box

99
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,833
which will hold 6 different foods

100
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:06,066
helping us cycle our diet

101
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,366
we can upgrade our crafting table in a crafting station

102
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:13,100

which will access nearby chests and hold items when closed


103
00:04:13,566 --> 00:04:16,366
we can also upgrade our chests using metals

104
00:04:16,466 --> 00:04:18,366
increasing the storage capacity

105
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,866
and by using a lot of cotton and leather

106
00:04:20,866 --> 00:04:23,400
we also managed to craft some backpacks

107
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,300
with all of that new equipment

108
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:30,266
,we can slowly work our way into harvesting a whole tree in the nearby forest

109
00:04:30,566 --> 00:04:34,233
another great tool of this age is the ore finder wand

110
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,466
to use it

111
00:04:35,466 --> 00:04:38,500
we insert a sample of something we want to find

112
00:04:38,766 --> 00:04:40,766
and then we just keep walking around

113
00:04:40,766 --> 00:04:42,900
until the wand starts to react

114
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:43,900
as you can see

115
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:47,066
you can even find diamonds just by searching for coal

116
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:50,633
and that's because there is always some coal around diamonds

117
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:54,833
the only thing left to do to complete this chapter is bronze

118
00:04:55,066 --> 00:04:58,100
to do so we collect some copper and some tin

119
00:04:58,366 --> 00:05:01,033
we grind those two materials into dust

120
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:03,100
and we mix everything up together

121
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,066
with that we have acquired bronze

122
00:05:05,066 --> 00:05:07,366
and we can move on to the next chapter

123
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,466
steam age

124
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,633
as the name suggests

125
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:13,400
here we are going to work with some steam machinery

126
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,433
starting from a small bronze boiler

127
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:17,200
to get our first steam

128
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:20,133
we pipe that into a steam alloy smelter

129
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:23,733
which will allow us to do some more advanced metals

130
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,200
such as red alloy

131
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:28,833
and that material is part of the complicated piston recipe

132
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:32,633
with pistons we can finally get to the useful machinery

133
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:33,966
starting from a macerator

134
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:40,133
which main feature is doubling the amount of materials we get when working raw ores

135
00:05:40,566 --> 00:05:42,566
since it doesn't get damage when used

136
00:05:42,566 --> 00:05:44,600
it can also spare our mortars

137
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:45,300
finally

138
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:48,000
it can also recycle the stuff we find in dungeons

139
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:49,900
talking of which

140
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:55,233
there are a lot of things we can collect or find in the various structures laying around the world

141
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:58,566
and the best material you can find is steel

142
00:05:58,966 --> 00:06:01,433
and by managing to collect 8 ingots

143
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:04,100
we can get some huge quality of life improvement

144
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:07,733
we use the first ingot to upgrade our pickaxes to steel

145
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,533
which can dig obsidian

146
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:12,300
we mix that with some steel and some aluminum

147
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,500
to obtain alumite

148
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,933
which we mold into larger plates

149
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:19,166
so that we can upgrade our tool station into Tool Forge

150
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,900
this upgrade will allow us to craft the most powerful and expensive tools

151
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,200
such as the lumber axe

152
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:29,033
which can chop down a whole tree in a single hit

153
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:32,366
or the hammer which is like 9 pickaxes

154
00:06:32,966 --> 00:06:34,033
with all of that stuff

155
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:35,966
we can now build heavier machinery

156
00:06:35,966 --> 00:06:37,433
such as the forge hammer

157
00:06:37,566 --> 00:06:40,033
which will allow us to get cheaper metal plates

158
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:43,933
however that great improvement came with a huge cost

159
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:45,800
a lot of steam

160
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:49,000
now there are many more ways of producing steam

161
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:51,233
but all of them have some heating times

162
00:06:51,233 --> 00:06:54,233
that won't play nicely with our consumption spikes

163
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:57,233
to fix those problems we made a huge buffer

164
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:01,333
a huge iron tank that can hold a lot of pressurized steam

165
00:07:02,366 --> 00:07:04,000
and by also getting a new boiler

166
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,300
we can now power some bigger machines

167
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,500
we start with a steam grinder

168
00:07:08,566 --> 00:07:10,233
which is like a macerator

169
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,200
but works 10 times faster while

170
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:14,133
being twice as power efficient

171
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,633
next we have the compressor multi block

172
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:20,133
finally and most importantly we have the steam presser

173
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:21,933
which does forge hammering

174
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:26,033
building the structure of those machines takes quite some materials

175
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,300
but we can reduce the cost

176
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,966
by having some of the parts being shared by different machines

177
00:07:31,566 --> 00:07:31,966
however

178
00:07:31,966 --> 00:07:35,433
running all of those at once is going to take a lot of steam

179
00:07:35,733 --> 00:07:38,100
and the issue is not our steam production

180
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:41,500
but how quickly we can convey it to the steam machines

181
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,166
that means we need better pipes for our steam

182
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:45,733
for that upgrade

183
00:07:45,733 --> 00:07:48,566
we can increase the size and use better materials

184
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:50,166
since we got in the basement

185
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:52,766
we also built a steam powered water pump

186
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:57,600
which will extract enough water to power the best steam generator in the game

187
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,833
the highest pressure solar boiler

188
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:02,333
now that energy is no longer an issue

189
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:05,366
we can start working on our next major project

190
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,933
a brick blast furnace

191
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:09,966
we start by shredding some bricks and some clay

192
00:08:09,966 --> 00:08:13,800
we mix this so obtained dusts to obtain a refractory compound

193
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:14,500
fire clay

194
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:18,500
we press that material into bricks with our steam compressor

195
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,000
then we heat blast those bricks

196
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,033
and after mixing up some concrete

197
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:26,400
we have the building blocks for our upcoming blast furnace

198
00:08:26,766 --> 00:08:29,833
the only issue left is to decide where to build it

199
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,600
and I mention that as an issue

200
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,200
because that machine is going to make pollution

201
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:38,700
I mean a single blast furnace isn't going to be much of a big deal

202
00:08:38,766 --> 00:08:41,166
but we will want to build more than one

203
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,900
and we will want to cut on the building costs

204
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:47,300
and once we had multiple of those running for a couple of hours

205
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:50,933
we can start to see and feel the effects of pollution

206
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:54,500
anyways now that we have managed to obtain steel

207
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,400
there are many things we can do with it

208
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,533
but first things first

209
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:00,400
now that we have steel and flint

210
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,833
we can visit the Nether

211
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,600
this place is filled with nasty creatures

212
00:09:04,766 --> 00:09:07,400
but it's the only place where we can find sulfur

213
00:09:07,766 --> 00:09:09,733
which we need to process rubber

214
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:10,433
meanwhile

215
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:13,400
we can use some steel to make a couple of molds

216
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:16,300
like the plate one to work rubber into sheets

217
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,733
with those we can craft piston boots

218
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:21,100
which will make moving around way easier

219
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,366
and at the cost of a single steel ring

220
00:09:23,366 --> 00:09:25,133
we can also get a better backpack

221
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,366
to carry around all of our tools

222
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:30,933
but the most useful thing we can craft with some more steel

223
00:09:30,933 --> 00:09:32,600
is a charcoal piling lighter

224
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:33,800
to use it

225
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:37,133
we first have to dig a huge hole with some bricks on the bottom

226
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:39,033
we fill that hole with logs

227
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:41,633
and after covering all of the wood with dirt

228
00:09:41,633 --> 00:09:44,166
we put our new machinery on top of it

229
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:46,133
this will start a long process

230
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:47,933
which will leave behind a lot of charcoal

231
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:50,833
that we can gather to fuel our blast furnaces

232
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,600
that will yield us a lot of steel

233
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,633
which we can use to craft some sturdy machine hulls

234
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,533
but those are just a supporting structure

235
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:01,366
to get any kind of task done

236
00:10:01,366 --> 00:10:03,200
we are going to need at least some motor

237
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,333
and some kind of control circuitry

238
00:10:05,766 --> 00:10:09,833
while motors are just a bunch of copper winding surrounding an iron core

239
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:12,166
circuits are more complicated

240
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:15,533
we start by laying some copper on a glued wooden board

241
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:15,966
next

242
00:10:15,966 --> 00:10:21,566
we make some improvised resistors and some vacuum tubes out of whatever we have at our disposal

243
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:22,200
finally

244
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,233
we add some steel parts and some red alloy cables

245
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:27,100
to obtain some basic circuitry

246
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,566
with all of that stuff

247
00:10:28,566 --> 00:10:30,500
we can build a steam turbine

248
00:10:30,566 --> 00:10:33,033
which will turn steam into electricity

249
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,666
after connecting the steam fuel line and the output cables

250
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:40,100
we can start adding the most basic machines to our workshop

251
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:44,200
but after getting a wiremill to increase our wire production yield

252
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,733
and a centrifuge to extract glue and gold

253
00:10:46,766 --> 00:10:51,033
we realized motors aren't enough for more intricate jobs

254
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:53,300
so we crafted a bunch more of components

255
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,500
that will unlock many more machines

256
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,833
but that's something we can see in the next episode

257
00:10:58,933 --> 00:10:59,833
bye bye

258
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,100
大家好

259
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:04,266
今天我们要开始新一季的GTNH

260
00:00:04,266 --> 00:00:06,233
不像上一季

261
00:00:06,366 --> 00:00:08,200
我们不会放弃任务书的

262
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:10,466
而是更严格地遵循它

263
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:12,833
我们被要求做的第一件事

264
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:14,200
就是收集一些泥土

265
00:00:14,233 --> 00:00:17,133
如果我们第一晚不能及时找到床

266
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:19,000
可以借助它挖三填一

267
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,633
但那不是问题

268
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:24,166
因为我们找到了可以藏身的废弃建筑

269
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:26,166
在那还找到了一张床

270
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:30,266
这可以使我们在进行下一任务前稍作歇息

271
00:00:30,266 --> 00:00:32,200
也就是找些木头和燧石

272
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,700
木头无处不在

273
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,266
但寻找燧石有点棘手

274
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:39,166
最简单的方法可能就是找一条河

275
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:40,300
并检查河床

276
00:00:40,566 --> 00:00:42,233
你可能会注意到一件事

277
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,033
不同于原版

278
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:46,300
你不会从沙砾获得燧石

279
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:47,466
要获取燧石

280
00:00:47,466 --> 00:00:50,233
你得把三块沙砾砸在一起

281
00:00:50,666 --> 00:00:52,633
这也是另一个任务

282
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:53,500
用那个燧石

283
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:56,366
我们现在可以制作一张相当昂贵的工作台

284
00:00:56,366 --> 00:00:58,000
还有一把斧头

285
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,500
燧石也将是我们第一批工具的材料

286
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,566
现在我们有了基本设备

287
00:01:03,566 --> 00:01:08,366
我们可以开始自我挑战的旅程，完成每一个任务

288
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:09,300
为此

289
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,433
我们不得不冒险穿越各种生物群落

290
00:01:12,866 --> 00:01:15,833
我们穿越干燥的生物群落寻找流沙

291
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:18,666
我们穿过湖泊去寻找魔法森林

292
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:21,466
那是唯一生长稀有蓝树的地方

293
00:01:21,566 --> 00:01:23,600
终于在穿过一个峡谷后

294
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:27,800
我们为最后一个任务找到了一片罕见竹林

295
00:01:27,966 --> 00:01:29,233
一旦我们回到家

296
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:33,800
就可以在进入下一章任务之前泡杯好茶

297
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:34,633
也就是T0电压

298
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,000
这是石器时代的水平

299
00:01:37,066 --> 00:01:39,766
所以我们必须从做一些繁重的工作开始

300
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,833
在收集到足够的材料后

301
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:44,433
我们可以为焦炉制作足够的砖块

302
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,233
我们会立刻把它建在地板下

303
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,466
这样用它给熔炉增添燃料会轻松不少

304
00:01:49,466 --> 00:01:51,866
那熔炉将为我们的房子擦亮石头

305
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:54,666
同时我们还建了一个小车间

306
00:01:54,666 --> 00:01:56,666
在那里我们可以制作更好的工具

307
00:01:57,666 --> 00:01:59,900
它由3张桌子组成

308
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:02,800
前两个将允许我们制作模板

309
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,633
和新工具的零件

310
00:02:04,866 --> 00:02:07,800
而我们可以使用各种易于成型的材料

311
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:09,966
这便是最后一张桌子的用途

312
00:02:09,966 --> 00:02:12,866
我们用来把零件组装成新工具

313
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,433
现在我们有了镐，是时候去采矿了

314
00:02:17,166 --> 00:02:18,866
但我们不会去找矿洞

315
00:02:18,866 --> 00:02:21,566
或者像原版MC一样随地打孔

316
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,800
在这个整合包中

317
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:26,466
矿石以网格形式成堆生成

318
00:02:27,066 --> 00:02:27,600
这意味着

319
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:30,200
我们只需要在区块中心挖掘

320
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,400
来寻找大矿脉

321
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:35,000
在这个地方我们发现了油砂

322
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,066
现在我们完全不需要它

323
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,166
所以我们继续找下一个

324
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:42,233
经过一番挖掘我们发现了褐铁矿

325
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,000
一种富含铁的矿物

326
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:47,233
但看起来我们的燧石镐挖不动

327
00:02:47,466 --> 00:02:47,900
幸运地

328
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:52,233
我们的任务书用圆石给了个铁镐头

329
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,900
我们用工具站修理镐子

330
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:57,600
再用新获得的部件升级它

331
00:02:58,566 --> 00:03:01,100
有了它，我们终于可以收集铁了

332
00:03:01,366 --> 00:03:04,233
我们新镐的另一个优点是

333
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:05,266
我们用得越多

334
00:03:05,266 --> 00:03:06,766
它就会升级得越多

335
00:03:06,966 --> 00:03:08,966
这将提供强化插槽

336
00:03:08,966 --> 00:03:12,933

这将使我们能够在工具中添加一些带有特殊效果的材料


337
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:13,666
例如

338
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:19,633
我们可以在镐中加入一些青金石来增加它收获的矿石量

339
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,166
另一个有用的材料是红石

340
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:26,100
这将提高我们工具的工作速度

341
00:03:26,233 --> 00:03:27,900
接下来我们建了一个冶炼厂

342
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,300
这是一个可变大小的结构

343
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,200
这将使我们能够熔化金属

344
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,300
并为我们的工具铸造零件

345
00:03:34,566 --> 00:03:38,133
但是像那样的工具只是用于基本的世界互动

346
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:40,466
要制造更先进的设备

347
00:03:40,466 --> 00:03:42,633
我们需要一些更精细的工具

348
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:44,233
这类工具很多

349
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:46,666
但我们可以从最基本的开始

350
00:03:47,266 --> 00:03:48,033
有了那些工具

351
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:50,966
我们现在可以用铁加工各种部件

352
00:03:51,466 --> 00:03:53,300
如果你想知道它们的用途

353
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,433
想想门是用螺丝固定在一起的

354
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,033
有了所有这些新零件

355
00:03:58,033 --> 00:04:00,033
我们现在可以制作许多新事物

356
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,100
我们可以从一个新的午餐盒开始

357
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,833
它将容纳6种不同的食物

358
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:06,066
帮助我们循环饮食

359
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,366
我们可以把工作台升级成合成站

360
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:13,100

它将连接到附近的箱子，并且能在关闭GUI时保留上面的物品


361
00:04:13,566 --> 00:04:16,366
我们也可以用金属升级箱子

362
00:04:16,466 --> 00:04:18,366
增加存储容量

363
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,866
通过使用大量的棉花和皮革

364
00:04:20,866 --> 00:04:23,400
我们还制作了一些背包

365
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,300
有了所有的新设备

366
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:30,266
我们可以在附近的森林慢慢地砍下一整棵树

367
00:04:30,566 --> 00:04:34,233
这个时代的另一个伟大工具是探矿魔杖

368
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,466
要使用它

369
00:04:35,466 --> 00:04:38,500
我们放入想寻找的矿物原矿

370
00:04:38,766 --> 00:04:40,766
然后我们就一直走来走去

371
00:04:40,766 --> 00:04:42,900
直到魔杖开始反应

372
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:43,900
如你所见

373
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:47,066
你甚至可以通过煤炭来找到钻石

374
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:50,633
那是因为钻石周围总是有一些煤

375
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:54,833
这一章要做的只剩下青铜了

376
00:04:55,066 --> 00:04:58,100
为此我们收集了一些铜和锡

377
00:04:58,366 --> 00:05:01,033
把它们磨成粉末

378
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:03,100
再把其混合在一起

379
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,066
这样我们就获得了青铜

380
00:05:05,066 --> 00:05:07,366
我们可以继续下一章

381
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,466
蒸汽时代

382
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,633
顾名思义

383
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:13,400
在这里，我们将使用一些蒸汽机械

384
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,433
从一个小青铜锅炉开始

385
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:17,200
得到我们的第一升蒸汽

386
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:20,133
我们把它输送到蒸汽合金冶炼炉

387
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:23,733
这将使我们能够制造一些更高级的金属

388
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,200
比如红色合金

389
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:28,833
这种材料是复杂活塞配方的一部分

390
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:32,633
有了活塞，我们终于可以做一些好机器了

391
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:33,966
从粉碎机开始

392
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:40,133
它可以使我们处理原矿获得二倍增产

393
00:05:40,566 --> 00:05:42,566
因为使用时不会损坏

394
00:05:42,566 --> 00:05:44,600
也能省下我们的研钵

395
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:45,300
最后

396
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:48,000
它还可以回收我们在地牢里找到的东西

397
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:49,900
说到地牢

398
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:55,233
我们可以在分布在世界各地的各种结构中获得大量材料

399
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:58,566
能找到的最好材料是钢

400
00:05:58,966 --> 00:06:01,433
我们设法收集了8个

401
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:04,100

将为我们的游戏体验上个档次


402
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:07,733
我们用第一个锭将镐升级为钢

403
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,533
它可以挖黑曜石

404
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:12,300
我们把它和一些钢和铝混合

405
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,500
获取锌曜钢/耐酸铝

406
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,933
我们把它塑造成大板

407
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:19,166
这样我们就可以将工具站升级为工具装配台

408
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,900
这次升级将使我们能够制作最强大、最昂贵的工具

409
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,200
比如伐木斧

410
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:29,033
一击就能砍倒一整棵树

411
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:32,366
或者是九镐合一的锤子

412
00:06:32,966 --> 00:06:34,033
有了所有这些东西

413
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:35,966
我们现在可以建造更“重”的机器

414
00:06:35,966 --> 00:06:37,433
比如锻造锤

415
00:06:37,566 --> 00:06:40,033
这将使我们能够减本增产板子

416
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:43,933
然而，巨大的进步伴随着巨大的成本

417
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:45,800
也就是大量蒸汽

418
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:49,000
现在有更多产生蒸汽的方法

419
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:51,233
但是它们都有一些暖机时间

420
00:06:51,233 --> 00:06:54,233
它们对耗能高峰有些乏力

421
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:57,233
为了解决这些问题，我们做了一个巨大的缓冲

422
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:01,333
一个可以容纳大量蒸汽的巨大铁罐

423
00:07:02,366 --> 00:07:04,000
并且借助于新的锅炉

424
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,300
我们现在可以驱动一些更大的机器

425
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,500
我们从蒸汽研磨机开始

426
00:07:08,566 --> 00:07:10,233

这就像粉碎机一样


427
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,200
但工作速度快10倍

428
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:14,133
两倍的能效

429
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,633
接下来是多方块压缩机

430
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:20,133
最后也是最重要的是蒸汽锻造锤

431
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:21,933
进行狠狠地砸击❤️

432
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:25,966
这些机器的结构方块需要相当多的材料

433
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:30,966
但我们可以通过共享一些结构方块降低成本

434
00:07:31,566 --> 00:07:31,966
然而

435
00:07:31,966 --> 00:07:35,433
同时运行它们会需要很多蒸汽

436
00:07:35,733 --> 00:07:38,100
问题不在于我们的蒸汽生产

437
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:41,500
而是输送到机器的速率

438
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,166
这意味着我们需要更好的蒸汽管道

439
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:45,733
对于那个升级

440
00:07:45,733 --> 00:07:48,566
我们可以增加尺寸并使用更好的材料

441
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:50,166
既然我们进了地下室

442
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:52,766
我们还建造了一个蒸汽驱动的水泵

443
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:57,600
它将提取足够的水来驱动游戏中最好的蒸汽发生器

444
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,833
†高级太阳能锅炉†

445
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:02,333
既然能源不再是问题

446
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:05,366
我们可以开始下一个大项目了

447
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,933
砖高炉

448
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:09,966
我们先粉碎一些砖块和粘土

449
00:08:09,966 --> 00:08:13,800
我们混合这种得到的粉尘得到一种耐火化合物

450
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:14,500
耐火粘土

451
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:18,500
我们用蒸汽压缩机将材料压成砖

452
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,000
然后我们对那些砖块进行熔炼

453
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,033
在混合了一些混凝土之后

454
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:26,400
我们为即将到来的高炉准备好了结构方块

455
00:08:26,766 --> 00:08:29,833
剩下的唯一问题是决定在哪里建造它

456
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,600
我把这认为是一个问题

457
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,200
是因为那台机器会制造污染

458
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:38,700
我是说一个高炉没什么大不了的

459
00:08:38,766 --> 00:08:41,166
但我们想要建造不止一个

460
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,900
我们会想削减建筑成本

461
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:47,300
一旦它们开始运行了几个小时

462
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:50,933

我们就可以开始感受到，甚至看到污染的后果


463
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:54,500
不管怎样，现在我们已经设法获得了钢铁

464
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,400
我们可以用它做很多事情

465
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,533
但首先

466
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:00,400

既然我们有了打火石


467
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,833
我们可以去下界了

468
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,600
这地方到处都是肮脏的生物

469
00:09:04,766 --> 00:09:07,400
但这是唯一能找到硫磺的地方

470
00:09:07,766 --> 00:09:09,733
我们用它来加工出橡胶

471
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:10,433
同时

472
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:13,400
我们可以用一些钢做几个模具

473
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:16,300
就像盘子一样，将橡胶加工成片材

474
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,733
有了这些，我们可以制作活塞靴

475
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:21,100
这将使四处走动更容易

476
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,366
以一个钢圈为代价

477
00:09:23,366 --> 00:09:25,133
我们也可以得到一个更好的背包

478
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,366
用来随身携带所有的工具

479
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:30,933
但我们能用钢铁制造的最有用的东西

480
00:09:30,933 --> 00:09:32,600
是木炭堆点火器

481
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:33,800
要使用它

482
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,733
我们首先要挖一个大洞

483
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:37,133
底部放一些砖块

484
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:39,033
我们用木头填满它

485
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:41,633
用泥土覆盖所有的木头后

486
00:09:41,633 --> 00:09:44,166
我们把新机器放在上面

487
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:46,133
这将开始一个漫长的过程

488
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:47,933
结束后产出大量木炭

489
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:50,833
我们将其收集好为高炉增添燃料

490
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,600

那样我们就能获得很多钢


491
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,633
我们可以用它来制作一些坚固机器外壳

492
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,533
但这些只是支撑结构

493
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:01,366
要完成各种类型的任务

494
00:10:01,366 --> 00:10:03,200
我们至少需要一些马达

495
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,333
和某种控制电路

496
00:10:05,766 --> 00:10:09,833
而马达只是一堆围绕铁芯的铜绕组

497
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:12,166
电路比较复杂

498
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:15,533
我们先在粘好的木板上放些铜

499
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:15,966
然后

500
00:10:15,966 --> 00:10:21,566
我们利用手头现有的材料制作了一些简易电阻和真空管

501
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:22,200
最后

502
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,233

我们加上一些钢外壳和一些红色合金电缆


503
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:27,100
获得一些基本电路

504
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,566
有了所有这些东西

505
00:10:28,566 --> 00:10:30,500
我们可以造一个蒸汽轮机

506
00:10:30,566 --> 00:10:33,033
这将把蒸汽转化为电能

507
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,666
连接蒸汽管道和输出电缆后

508
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:40,100
我们可以开始为车间添加LV机器

509
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:44,200
但是在得到一个线缆轧机来提高线材产量后

510
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,733
以及一个离心机用来提取胶水和金

511
00:10:46,766 --> 00:10:51,033
我们意识到马达不足以完成更复杂的工作

512
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:53,300
所以我们制作了更多的组件

513
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,500
这将解锁更多的机器

514
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,833

但这就将是下期的内容了


515
00:10:58,933 --> 00:10:59,833
拜拜

516
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:26,466
（3*3区块对应一个格雷矿脉）

